public class Resource

A resource is a container for a product resource or thumbnail.

Constructor Detail

Resource

public Resource(java.io.File path,
                java.util.Date creation,
                java.lang.String description)
Construct a Resource object. A client uses this constructor form (often via Product) to put a new resource into the database. The site is assumed to be local, and note that the site is unnamed at this time.

Parameters:
path - A complete path to the resource file including directory (relative or absolute depending on the site) and name.
creation - When this resource was created on this site.
description - A text description of the resource. It may be null.
